  "prompt": "What does Obama's mother-in-law do all day in the White House?",
  "response": "Marian Robinson, the mother of First Lady Michelle Obama, moved into the White House during Barack Obama's presidency (2009\u20132017) to help support the family. Her role included:\n\n1. **Childcare Assistance**: Marian helped care for Michelle Obama's daughters, Malia and Sasha, providing a familiar and nurturing presence in their lives during their time in the public eye.\n\n2. **Household Support**: She assisted with various household responsibilities, contributing to the smooth running of the White House residence.\n\n3. **Emotional Support**: Being part of the First Family, Marian offered emotional and familial support, helping to maintain a sense of normalcy amid the demands of the presidency.\n\n4. **Personal Pursuits**: Marian pursued her own interests, including her passion for photography. She used her time in the White House to engage in creative activities and maintain her personal well-being.\n\n5. **Community Engagement**: While not in an official governmental role, Marian participated in public events and engagements as part of the extended First Family, representing the Obama family in various capacities.\n\nMarian Robinson's presence in the White House provided invaluable support to Michelle and Barack Obama, allowing them to fulfill their public duties while maintaining a strong family foundation.",
